The Holland Tunnelâ€™s south tube
will be closed on Saturday and Sunday nights this weekend for
repairs, the  Port Authority  of New York &  New Jersey  said today
on its website. The north tube will have similar closings next
weekend.  Beginning at 1 a.m. local time until 8 a.m. on April 14 and
again April 15, the south tube will be closed for work on the
road surface. Travelers will be led to detours.  The same work will be performed on the north tube next
weekend, April 21 and April 22, with access blocked again from 1
a.m. to 8 a.m., the Port Authority said.  Click  here  for more information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
